    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors were assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed the required gradation level for a Medium model risk, Medium model influence, Medium decision consequence context. The single gap (Test conditions, achieved level 1 vs. required level 2) is accepted based on the standardized and widely-validated nature of the ASTM F1717 protocol and the corroborating evidence from two independent test laboratories. Quantitative validation metrics (E/uval < 1.96 and percent difference < 10%) are satisfied for all three QoIs. The FEA modeling framework is accepted as sufficiently credible to support regulatory decision-making for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design.",
